40|$|This essay {{considers}} the cultural fears and anxieties that are portrayed in Edgar Allan Poe’s The Narrative of Arthur Gordon Pym. Drawing upon Tsalal’s natural hesitancy for nature to intermingle with itself, {{in addition to}} the tragically brutal clashing of white and <b>black</b> <b>cultures,</b> Poe highlights 19 th-century United States’ desire for segregation between North and South, while also depicting southern slave owners’ looming fear of slave uprisings...|$|R
